    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      LinkedList<Event> getEvents() 
      void run()
      for each selected window to be run, - assign the corresponding signals to the partNt and partNwt - with the construction of the KeyWord, all the needed computations are done - theta1 will be used to filter the keywords - For each window, it has big correlation matrix of the remaining keywords - The matrix will be filtered with the threshold theta2 - for each window, some events will be detected using the modularity detection

        Parameters:
        window - number of the window
        sizeWindow_ - size of the window
        longKeyWords_ - the whole KeyWord of the specified folder
        delta_ - parameter, input form the user, defined in the 'param' file
        gamma1_ - parameter, input form the user, defined in the 'param' file (should be >10)
        gamma2_ - parameter, input form the user, defined in the 'param' file (should be >10)
        thresholdE_ - parameter, input form the user, defined in the 'param' file
        debugMode_ - if debug mode enabled, it will store some files in the hard drive.
        nwtFolder_ - path to folder containing the nwt files.

        public void run()
        for each selected window to be run, - assign the corresponding signals to the partNt and partNwt - with the construction of the KeyWord, all the needed computations are done - theta1 will be used to filter the keywords - For each window, it has big correlation matrix of the remaining keywords - The matrix will be filtered with the threshold theta2 - for each window, some events will be detected using the modularity detection
